race.comment: MARINE GIRL (12) gave a bold sight first-up at Queanbeyan but just lacked fitness and was collared late. Better with that run under her belt and will prove much tougher to reel in this time. CHICO CASINO (3) hasn't been beaten far in his two runs back and goes well third-up. Is drawn to advantage and keeps the claimer on to help under the big weight. Expect him to be in this for a long way. MY CROWN (16) was only fair when resuming at Gunnedah but is a likely improver, and already a track and trip winner at this venue. Worth some thought. KOBOLD (9) resumes and looks best of the rest. Gallagher's booking.
